      "content": "interesting. so if the main goal is to keep things stable and stick to the text, how do originalists handle cases involving rights that aren't explicitly mentioned in the Constitution, like privacy or technology stuff? like, do they just say 'it's not in the text so it doesn't exist' or is there a more nuanced way they justify it?",
